n\in\left\{1,2,\dots\right\}
X_0, X_1, \dots, X_n
\mathrm{Bernouli}(p)
p\in\left(\frac{1}{2},1\right)
S:=\sum_{i=0}^n X_i
\mu:=E[S]
q
\frac{n}{2}
i
\left\{X_i=1\right\}
q=1-P\left(S\leq\frac{n}{2}\right)
\mu=np
1-e^{-\frac{1}{2p}n\left(p-\frac{1}{2}\right)^2}
P\left(S\leq\frac{n}{2}\right)=P\left(S\leq\left(1-\left(1-\frac{1}{2p}\right)\right)\mu\right)\leq e^{-\frac{\mu}{2}\left(1-\frac{1}{2p}\right)^2}=e^{-\frac{1}{2p}n\left(p-\frac{1}{2}\right)^2}
